            <title>[THRIFT-186] Erlang Makefile not compatible with Solaris</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-186</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The sed lines in lib/erl/src/Makefile weren&apos;t happy on solaris. Here&apos;s a replacement for them:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MODULES = $(shell find . -name &amp;#42;.erl | sed &apos;s:^&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;./::&apos; | sed &apos;s/\.erl//&apos;)&lt;br/&gt;
MODULES_STRING_LIST = $(shell find . -name &amp;#42;.erl | sed &apos;s:^\./:&quot;:&apos; | sed &apos;s/\.erl/&quot;,/&apos;)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Marking patch available even though it&apos;s not a strict patch. Hopefully that&apos;s ok cuz it&apos;s like 4 characters &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
